# URL rewrite for the static site on Cloudflare Pages.
#
# Cloudflare Pages serves clean URLs natively, so most paths need no rule:
#   /today                              -> today.html
#   /snapshots/world_cup_tracker_DATE   -> the matching .html snapshot
# The only thing Pages can't infer is the bare root, because the tracker file is
# not named index.html - so map "/" to it. (Do NOT add an explicit
# "/today -> /today.html" rule: Pages also canonicalises /today.html back to
# /today, so that rule creates an infinite redirect loop.)
#
# 200 = rewrite: the file is served while the address bar keeps the clean URL.

/   /world_cup_tracker.html   200
